messages.message:
Patch Set 1: Verified-1 Code-Review-2

There are still many wrong things in your chain:

1. Your "get rid of blur and visualizer" commits have no reason
to be merged because they can already be disabled, if they don't
please your eyes. You don't nuke features just because you don't like
them, so no, we're not merging those - you can still use them in your
builds if having that visualizer and blur code inside the app bothers you.
2. Again, your coding style is still wrong, you are still using tabs
instead of 4 spaces and there are still random whitespace additions.
3. The settings commit is still wrong; you are missing Android.mk and 
java changes.
4. The "artworks" are in an higher quality than the current one for
sure, but the shadows are just physically wrong (and tbh make no sense).
5. Again, you've included the constraintLayout support library, what's
the point? Use the androidx version, support libraries have been deprecated
and have been unmaintained for the last two years. And eleven switched to
androidx libraries last year too.

Patch Set 1:

One more thing: Gerrit is not Imgur, when I asked for
screenshots, I never intended them to be literally uploaded to Gerrit.

Usually, when someone does a UI-related change it's usually shown off in internal
channels first (eg. slack), and then the code uploaded to Gerrit.
When there it's a new contributor that makes it, usually they put a comment
with a link to a set of pictures that show the difference before and
after the commit. But they use proper image hosting websites.

Gerrit is for submitting code contributions: please use any other image
hosting website (eg. imgur.com or google photos) for this purpose.
